passes (e.g., 3/4) still advance ROADMAP. Criteria:\n1. **Live pane monitoring** — harness shows live content of all agent tmux panes\n2. **Orchestrator intervention** — orchestrator can `send-keys` to any pane\n3. **Session persistence** — harness restart preserves `paused`/`detached` sessions\n4. **Visual dependency graph** — delegation tree renders as a pane grid (DFS via P51 `grid-planner.ts`)\n\n**Tests**: 4 BATS scenarios + 1 manual screenshot/journal pass for visual verification.\n**L1 evidence**: 4 BATS files, each running in isolation; L2 evidence: manual screenshots of the tmux grid + journal entries.\n**GATE**: All 4 BATS must run; 3/4 PASS advances ROADMAP, 2/4 or fewer requires P56 retry phase.\n**Requirements:** REQ-04, REQ-05, REQ-07.\n**Depends on:** Phase 54.\n\n## SPEC.md STRUCTURE (match P54 format)\n\n### 4 EARS (one per seed criterion)\n\n- REQ-55-01: Live pane monitoring BATS — verify `.hivemind/journal/test-session/<ISO>-pane.json` is written by `pane-monitor` hook when tmux session emits `pane-captured` event (P53 integration)\n- REQ-55-02: Orchestrator intervention BATS — verify `tmux-copilot` tool can `send-keys` to a specific tmux pane; the receiving tmux session shows the keys\n- REQ-55-03: Session persistence BATS — verify harness restart preserves `paused`/`detached` sessions; spawn tmux session, persist state, kill harness, restart, verify session still alive (P54 integration)\n- REQ-55-04: Visual dependency graph BATS — verify `grid-planner.ts` produces a DFS pane layout given a delegation tree; check pane coordinates form a valid grid\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] BATS `57-live-pane-monitoring.bats` runs and produces journal entry file\n- [ ] BATS `58-orchestrator-intervention.bats` runs and `tmux-copilot send-keys` succeeds\n- [ ] BATS `59-session-persistence-restart.bats` runs and tmux session survives harness restart\n- [ ] BATS `60-visual-dependency-graph.bats` runs and `grid-planner.computeSplitSequence` returns valid DFS layout\n- [ ] All 4 BATS pass individually (or 3/4 per gate logic)\n- [ ] Manual L2 evidence captured in `55-E2E-UAT-2026-06-02.md` (screenshots of tmux grid + journal entries)\n- [ ] GATE: 3/4 PASS advances ROADMAP to P56+; 2/4 or fewer triggers P56 retry phase planning\n\n## CONTEXT.md DECISIONS (10-12)\n\n- D-55-01: BATS file naming `57-..`, `58-..`, `59-..`, `60-..` (slot reservation per P50/P51/P52/P53/P54 pattern)\n- D-55-02: Each BATS in isolation (`bats --jobs 1 tests/scripts/tmux/5X-*.bats`)\n- D-55-03: L1 evidence = BATS pass output; L2 evidence = manual screenshot/journal (text-described in `55-E2E-UAT-2026-06-02.md`)\n- D-55-04: GATE logic: 3/4 PASS = advance; 2/4 = P56 retry; partial pass (2/4 with at least 1 of criteria 1+2) gets 7-day grace period per close-pivot\n- D-55-05: Real OS process survival (no mocks); per P54 D-54-12 precedent\n- D-55-06: BATS pattern: `load \"helpers\"` + `tmux_bats_require_dist` + `tmux_node_eval` for ESM module invocation\n- D-55-07: Each BATS uses `BATS_TEST_TMPDIR` for isolation; cleanup with `tmux kill-session` in teardown\n- D-55-08: BATS timing tolerance: ±100ms for backoff/scheduling tests; no tolerance for persistence tests\n- D-55-09: 55-E2E-UAT-2026-06-02.md format: 1 section per criterion with L1 (BATS output) + L2 (screenshot/journal) + verdict per criterion\n- D-55-10: SC-isolation: no SC-* work referenced; rootSessionId separation enforced\n- D-55-11: Atomic commits (no intermediate commits); 1 commit for SPEC+CONTEXT, 1 commit for 4 BATS, 1 commit for UAT report + STATE/ROADMAP\n- D-55-12: 27 tool keys unchanged (no new tool registrations — P55 is verification only)\n\n## OUTPUT FORMAT\n\nMatch `54-SPEC.md` and `54-CONTEXT.md` structure. Use the EARS methodology for SPEC. Use the Locked Decisions table for CONTEXT.\n\n## DELIVERABLE\n\nWrite BOTH files:\n1. `55-SPEC.md` (4 EARS, ambiguity ≤0.20)\n2. `55-CONTEXT.md` (12 decisions)\n\nCommit each separately:\n```bash\ngit add .planning/phases/55-e2e-uat-against-seed-success-criteria/55-SPEC.md\ngit commit -m \"P55 Checkpoint 4: 55-SPEC.md — 4 EARS, composite ambiguity 0.xx\"\n\ngit add .planning/phases/55-e2e-uat-against-seed-success-criteria/55-CONTEXT.md\ngit commit -m \"P55 Checkpoint 5: 55-CONTEXT.md — 12 decisions locked\"\n```\n\n## EXECUTION DISCIPLINE\n\n1. **USE TOOLS** — every step uses Read/Write/Bash.\n2. **DO NOT** modify source files; only the 2 planning files.\n3. **DO NOT** touch `.hivemind/session-tracker/*` (R-P50-03).\n4. **SC-isolation**: no SC-* references.\n5. **YIELD** when both commits are on disk.\n\nWhen complete, return:\n```\n###TASK_COMPLETED###\nP55 SPEC: 4 EARS, ambiguity 0.xx\nP55 CONTEXT: 12 decisions\nCommits: <hash1>, <hash2>\n```",
